Preheat your oven to 200°C. Halve the @yellow pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve, peel and finely slice the @red onion{1}. Trim the @courgette{1}, then halve lengthways. Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Put the pepper on a #baking tray{}.

Drizzle the peppers with @oil{drizzle} and sprinkle over the @Caribbean style jerk{1}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat and spread out. Pop the @caramelised onion sausages{4} on top of the peppers. 

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Roast the sausages and veg on the top shelf until the veg are soft and the sausages cooked, ~{25-30%minutes}. Halfway through cooking add the courgette, give the tray a shake and put it back in your oven.

Meanwhile, put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the potato. Peel and chop the @potato{1} into roughly 2cm pieces and add to your pan of boiling water. Cook until soft, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and season with @salt{}, cook the onion until soft, ~{8-10%minutes}. Add the @water{150%ml} with the @chicken stock powder{1}, stir to dissolve and bring to a simmer. Add the @mango chutney{1}, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(chopped, stalks and all). Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{1%splash}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Stir through the parsley.

> If the potatoes are cooked before the sausage and veggies, simply put a lid on the pan to keep it warm until everything else is ready.

Reheat the gravy if you need to. When the sausages are browned and cooked, and the veggies are soft, take the baking tray out of your oven.

> IMPORTANT: The sausage is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Serve the mash with the sausage and veggies with the mango chutney gravy on top. Enjoy!